explanation: No additional symbols are required. The MISRA rule in question prohibits modifying a function's own parameters. OS_TaskExit has no parameters in its signature, so it cannot violate that rule by modifying a parameter. All variables modified in the body are local (task_id, token) or occur inside called functions; modifications inside callees apply to those functions' own parameters and are not relevant to whether OS_TaskExit modifies its own parameters. Passing &token to callees is not a modification of OS_TaskExit parameters (there are none). Therefore no extra symbol definitions are needed to determine compliance.
